WEBVTT

00:01.293 --> 00:04.649
The Carmichael Show is taped in
front of a live studio audience.

00:04.650 --> 00:07.852
- Bobby, are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

00:07.853 --> 00:12.056
Well, how'd you get
yourself electrocuted, son?

00:12.057 --> 00:13.858
You didn't put a George Foreman Grill

00:13.859 --> 00:16.760
on the edge of your tub again, did you?

00:18.029 --> 00:20.064
I told you, Bobby, burgers can wait

00:20.065 --> 00:23.367
until after you're done with your bath.

00:23.368 --> 00:26.404
No, no, no. I was at work,
and my boss had me

00:26.405 --> 00:28.039
rewiring the lights in the lobby.

00:28.040 --> 00:30.374
Yeah, but you're not an
electrician, you are a super.

00:30.375 --> 00:31.843
The only thing you're
supposed to be doing

00:31.844 --> 00:35.446
is looking for mold
and evicting prostitutes.

00:35.447 --> 00:37.982
Okay, Bobby, I hope you're
all right and everything,

00:37.983 --> 00:40.151
but I got $100 riding on this.

00:40.152 --> 00:43.521
Were you trying to cook
burgers in the bathtub again?

00:43.522 --> 00:46.190
No, okay? Will somebody
give me some credit?

00:46.191 --> 00:47.725
I gave you credit, Bobby,

00:47.726 --> 00:50.061
and it won me $100.

00:50.062 --> 00:52.063
Man, I hate my job.

00:52.064 --> 00:54.432
I'm just not cut out
to be fixing things.

00:54.433 --> 00:55.767
As soon as he touched those wires,

00:55.768 --> 00:57.401
he shot across the room.

00:57.402 --> 01:00.505
Made me realize how scared
I am of the police.

01:00.506 --> 01:01.873
He was unconscious for seven minutes,

01:01.874 --> 01:05.176
and I still didn't call 911.

01:05.177 --> 01:07.445
Come here, baby.
Now, hold on now, Cynt.

01:07.446 --> 01:10.548
We got to make sure all the
electricity is out of him.

01:10.549 --> 01:11.582
(alarmed shouts)

01:11.583 --> 01:13.084
(laughter)

01:13.085 --> 01:15.119
I got you on that, didn't I?

01:15.120 --> 01:17.020
- I just reached out...
- (shouting)

01:19.624 --> 01:22.593
I guess it's time to charge my phone.

01:22.594 --> 01:24.661
(shouting)

01:29.066 --> 01:32.637
Joe, you are so good
at lightening the mood.

01:32.638 --> 01:34.639
(sarcastically): Ha ha!

01:34.640 --> 01:37.875
Okay, when I was laying
on death's door,

01:37.876 --> 01:41.612
I realized that my life
hasn't meant anything so far,

01:41.613 --> 01:44.148
and that if I died today,
I wouldn't have anything

01:44.149 --> 01:46.717
to leave behind but
three pair of Jordans

01:46.718 --> 01:49.787
and this Apple Watch.

01:49.788 --> 01:51.956
Dammit, Bobby,
you stole my Apple Watch.

01:51.957 --> 01:54.559
Well, it's mine now,
and it's all I got.

01:54.560 --> 01:56.494
Uh-oh.

01:56.495 --> 01:58.062
What's going on, Nekeisha?

01:58.063 --> 01:59.931
I posted on Facebook to pray for Bobby

01:59.932 --> 02:02.600
'cause he hurt himself,
and most people misunderstood

02:02.601 --> 02:04.602
and think he tried to commit suicide.

02:04.603 --> 02:06.904
Dammit, Nekeisha.

02:06.905 --> 02:09.574
Oh, look, they set up a memorial fund.

02:09.574 --> 02:11.576
Oh, that's nice.

02:11.577 --> 02:14.278
That's so nice. Every little bit helps.

02:14.279 --> 02:16.113
Look at these comments.

02:16.114 --> 02:19.984
"RIP Bobby." "Sad day."

02:19.985 --> 02:23.521
"The signs were all there"?

02:23.522 --> 02:27.390
Why does everybody think
I tried to kill myself?

02:29.460 --> 02:30.962
Hello, I'm Dr. Hunt.

02:30.963 --> 02:33.865
Doctor, this isn't gonna
cause some kind of

02:33.866 --> 02:36.534
long-term erectile dysfunction, is it?

02:36.535 --> 02:38.002
Mom!

02:38.003 --> 02:41.105
I want grandbabies.

02:41.106 --> 02:42.506
There's nothing to worry about.

02:42.507 --> 02:44.609
All his test results came back fine.

02:44.610 --> 02:46.277
Just be careful out
there next time, okay?

02:46.278 --> 02:49.614
All right, man. Thank you, Doc... Wait.

02:49.615 --> 02:51.515
Darnell Hunt?

02:51.516 --> 02:52.516
Darnell Hunt from Reynolds High?

02:52.517 --> 02:53.885
Yes.

02:53.886 --> 02:55.219
It's me, man Bobby Carmichael.

02:55.220 --> 02:56.621
We was in the same class.

02:56.622 --> 02:57.989
Oh, yeah, I remember you.

02:57.990 --> 02:59.457
You used to date that
girl in the wheelchair.

02:59.458 --> 03:03.995
Yeah, that's something I did briefly.

03:03.996 --> 03:06.197
How are you old enough to be a doctor?

03:06.198 --> 03:08.199
Well, after high school
I did four years of college,

03:08.200 --> 03:09.867
then four years of medical school,

03:09.868 --> 03:11.135
then two years of residency

03:11.136 --> 03:12.670
and one year of internship.

03:12.671 --> 03:13.871
And I've been practicing medicine

03:13.872 --> 03:15.172
the last five years.

03:15.173 --> 03:16.674
I'm 34, just like you.

03:16.675 --> 03:19.911
Oh, yeah. (chuckles)

03:19.912 --> 03:21.879
Okay, I got to go.

03:21.880 --> 03:22.980
It was good seeing you, Bobby.

03:22.981 --> 03:24.916
Take care, everybody.

03:24.917 --> 03:26.984
A young, black doctor.

03:26.985 --> 03:29.253
I bet he drives a Tesla.

03:29.254 --> 03:34.725
I get so proud when I see
black people driving Teslas.

03:34.726 --> 03:38.663
Man, seeing how great Darnell's doing

03:38.664 --> 03:39.997
makes me feel like a loser.

03:39.998 --> 03:43.133
Don't say that, Bobby.
His name is Dr. Hunt.

03:44.035 --> 03:46.237
All right, that settles it.

03:46.238 --> 03:48.940
I know what I got to do.

03:48.941 --> 03:51.242
Bobby Carmichael is going to college.

03:51.243 --> 03:53.344
(laughing)

03:53.345 --> 03:54.912
Well, come on, y'all,

03:54.913 --> 03:57.248
laugh at the boy's joke
about going to college.

03:57.249 --> 04:00.150
Don't hurt his feelings.

04:02.720 --> 04:04.988
